review_blob: Might have been better if it wasnt so cold. It lost a bit of its taste because it was so icey.

beer_brewer_name: Wild Goose Brewery (Frederick Brewing Company/Flying Dog)
review_blob: I am not exactly sure about this rating because I got the beer just after the new year and the label said best if drank by 2007. It still tasted nice and IPA-like to me.

Moosehead has such a smooth finish.  The initial taste is good enough, and then unlike many beers I drank in my early years, it finishes very clean and crisp. Pretty regular beer though, nothing too special about it, except for the fact that my uncle told me and my friends when we were 12 to get a case of it and go off into the woods and get drunk.

I am a huge fan of PBR. I know that many people think that it is trash. I cant get past it. It is probably because I have drank so much of it this year due to monetary issues, and Ive grown to love it. Whatever it is, I like it.
It initially has that nice bitter taste, then it goes on to chocolate. Just when you think it is done morphing it gives you that kick because of its 10.6 alcohol by volume.
